                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In late November 1952, the Haitian Government and the Export-Import Bank reached
                    a settlement with respect to <gloss target="#t_SHADA1">SHADA</gloss>. The terms
                    of the settlement included, <hi rend="italic">inter alia</hi>, provisions easing
                    Haiti’s repayment obligations on the <gloss target="#t_SHADA1">SHADA</gloss>
                    loan, the transfer of <gloss target="#t_SHADA1">SHADA</gloss> stock held by the
                    Bank to the Haitian Government, and Haitian control and management of <gloss
                        target="#t_SHADA1">SHADA</gloss> (despatch 374, from Port-au-Prince, dated
                    November 28, 1952, 838.20/11–2852). The terms were incorporated into a letter
                    from Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GHE1">Gaston</persName> to Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJ1">Léger</persName>, dated November 26, 1952, no copy of which
                    was found in Department of State files.</p>
            </div>
